Scenarios where hf2 was >0.1 showed greater power and robustness. This was particularly evident in the cluster causal model where power was over 0.7 for all dilution sets in scenarios with hf2 = 0.5 and h2 = 0.20 (Fig. 1). The only parameter for which the estimation deteriorated with increasing h2f was the partitioning of genomic variance between the markers included in the genomic feature and the remaining markers for the dilution sets (estimated \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
